{{Infobox language |name=Gavião of Jiparaná |nativename=Gavião of Rondônia |states= [[Brazil]] |ethnicity=[[Gavião (Rondônia)|Gavião]] – 520 (2004)<ref name=e18/> |speakers=340 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Tupian languages|Tupian]] |fam2=[[Monde languages|Monde]] |dia1=Zoró |iso3=gvo |glotto=gavi1246 |glottorefname=Gavião Do Jiparaná }}
'''Gaviao of Jiparana''' (''Gavião do Jiparaná''), also known as Digüt, Ikolen and ''Gavião do Rondônia'', is the language of the [[Gavião (Rondônia)|Gavião]] of [[Rondônia]], [[Brazil]]. It is a [[Tupian language]] of the [[Monde languages|Monde]] branch. It is partially intelligible with [[Suruí language|Suruí]]. The '''Zoró''' dialect is sometimes considered a separate language.
