'''Waurá''' (Wauja) is an [[Arawakan languages|Arawakan language]] spoken in [[Brazil]]. It is "partially [[mutually intelligible|intelligible]]" with [[Mehináku language|Mehináku]]. The entire population speaks the language.<ref name=e18/>
